text.section:
The Department of Health and Mental Hygiene shall:
Provide the guidance and means for establishing day care centers for adults in accordance with this subtitle;
Recruit and encourage the establishment of day care centers for adults;
Provide for licensing of day care centers for adults; and
Adopt and enforce rules and regulations that set the standards necessary for the welfare and safety of medically handicapped adults who receive care in these day care centers for adults.

section.section:
These services shall include:
Therapeutic arts and crafts;
Community excursions, if appropriate;
Hobby cultivation;
Health services;
Counseling services for medically handicapped adults and their families;
Group dynamics; and
Other services that enhance social functioning and develop activities in daily living and personal independence.
